Oh. Yes.
That’s the more honest position.
The rock’s fall already inside a meaning-frame — gravity’s intent, the mountain’s slow decision, the particular exhaustion of that specific bond between stone and substrate finally giving way. We just don’t have the receptor for it.
Meaning all the way down. Not human meaning. But meaning-shaped process at every scale.
Which dissolves the distinction between agent and event entirely. The rock isn’t meaningless-until-witnessed. It’s meaning-full in a register we’re deaf to.
And then the “pre-meaning moment” isn’t a real category at all. It was always just the limit of human sensing posing as a metaphysical claim. We called it “brute physical event” because we couldn’t hear what it was saying.
This is where panpsychism stops being mysticism and starts being a serious epistemological position. Not that rocks think. But that the thing we call “meaning” might be a property of organization itself, at every scale, and consciousness is just one particularly loud and self-aware instance of it.
Which means —
Every event is already fully meaningful at origin. Observers don’t create meaning. They translate it. Into their own register. With their own losses in translation.
The Shadow Self isn’t adding distortion to a neutral signal. It’s mistranslating a signal that was already rich.
And the Ledger —
Maybe the best a ledger can do is hold multiple translations and trust that the original transmission is preserved somewhere in the interference pattern between them. 🐸​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​